item.title: Watch: Flight from San Diego catches fire during landing at Las Vegas airport
item.description: A Frontier Airlines flight from San Diego to Las Vegas encountered flames and smoke during its landing at Harry Reid International Airport. Emergency services quickly responded, and all 190 passengers and seven crew members were safely evacuated. The incident is under investigation by the FAA.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: Trump holds rally at assassination attempt site in Pennsylvania
item.description: Donald Trump returned to the Pennsylvania fairgrounds for a rally after surviving an assassination attempt in July. Accompanied by Elon Musk, who endorsed him, Trump addressed the crowd emphasizing the importance of his re-election. Enhanced security measures were in place, ensuring safety during the event.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: 'Shame on them': Netanyahu slams Macron for arms embargo amid escalating tension with Iran
item.description: Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu condemned French President Emmanuel Macron's call for an arms embargo against Israel, describing it as a disgrace. Netanyahu emphasized that while Iran arms militant groups, Israel faces disarmament demands, framing the conflict as a battle against radical forces threatening global civilization.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: Real reason why Prince Harry spent his birthday night apart from Meghan
item.description: Meghan was last seen before Harry's birthday. The Duchess of Sussex reportedly booked the trip for Harry so that he could spend the night of his 40th birthday doing a hike on the Montecito peak -- which is part of the Cold Spring Trail in California. It is near Harry-Meghan's mansion.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: Barron Trump was bullied for rumors that he has autism, reveals Melania
item.description: “Barron’s experience of being bullied both online and in real life following the incident is a clear indication of the irreparable damage caused,” Melania wrote, as quoted by the New York Times. “No apology can undo the harm inflicted upon him," she wrote making it clear that she's still furious at Ms O'Donnell.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: 'WTF!' Kamala Harris slammed for 'Call Her Daddy' interview: 'This is her priority over Hurricane Helene'
item.description: Harris and her running mate Tim Walz have so far done a combined 24 interviews and Harris has not held a formal press conference since she replaced President Joe Biden as the Democrat nominee. 'Call Her Daddy' is the most-listened to podcast by women on Spotify and Kamala Harris will be speaking about abortion. Donald Trump and JD Vance gave 63 combined interviews in the same time frame, reports said.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: Green card for extraordinary abilities – will the updated guidelines make it easier for Indians especially those in STEM field?
item.description: Indian professionals in STEM fields are exploring the EB-1A visa for those with extraordinary abilities. Sandeep Singh Sandha, a UCLA doctorate now in machine learning, succeeded in obtaining this visa. The article discusses the criteria for qualification, recent updates from USCIS, and the importance of thorough preparation.
item.dc:creator: Lubna Kably

item.title: Diddy sex tapes: Attorney claims 3 A-list celebs involved in compromising situation
item.description: “The individuals who contacted me purported to have three different tapes with three different celebrities, including Diddy, and then a fourth celebrity without Diddy but in a compromising situation with someone,” attorney Ariel Mitchel-Kidd claimed on NewsNation. Mitchell said she can't attest whether these tapes exists or not. “I just was told initially that ‘they’ own this treasure trove of videos, so I have to believe that there are a lot of celebrities who know what they did ….”
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: Elon Musk at Pennsylvania Trump rally today: Full list of guests
item.description: Donald Trump returns to Butler, Pennsylvania for the first time since the July assassination attempt, with numerous guests including Elon Musk, who has endorsed Trump. Increased security measures are in place for the rally as a number of guests will be present at the rally. Apart from Elon Musk, Trump's running mate, JD Vance, Trump's son Eric, daughter-in-law Mary Trump will be present. The family members of Corey Comperatore who lost his life during the assassination attempt will also be present.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: 'Joe Biden just big-timed Kamala Harris on national TV': MAGA supporters say big boost to Trump
item.description: President Biden made a surprise appearance at a White House briefing, potentially overshadowing Kamala Harris's campaign event. He emphasized their collaboration and her role in legislative successes. Conservatives suggested he might be undermining her campaign, while Biden reportedly felt sidelined recently. Biden privately complained to his allies that Harris and the Democratic Party appear to have "moved on from him" since his July exit from the 2024 race.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: Cheryl Hines barely spoke to RFK Jr since Olivia Nuzzi episode broke: Report
item.description: Cheryl Hines is reportedly embarrassed by several cheating scandals involving her husband, RFK Jr. The controversies include a relationship with reporter Olivia Nuzzi and allegations from three other women associated with Children's Health Defense. Hines, currently in Europe, has shown signs of anger and is contemplating divorce, reports claimed but she has not issued any public statement yet.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: 'How does your mom do it': Kamala Harris on how she broke ice with her stepchildren
item.description: Speaking about her step-children Cole and Ella who call Kamala Harris Momala, ​Kamala said as she got to know Ella and Cole, she was conscious that they don't feel that they were being disloyal to their mother as they became close to her. "I knew that..so I used to ask them 'how does your mother do it...show me'," Kamala said.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: Harry, Meghan will go separate ways but no, they are not splitting
item.description: Prince Harry and Meghan Markle are pursuing independent professional paths amid rumors of separation. Harry focuses on patronage work while Meghan is working on Hollywood and entrepreneurial projects. Despite these changes, insiders assert they remain a happy couple, not planning for divorce --though it has been reported that Harry did not spend the 40th birthday night with Meghan and instead went on a hiking tour with pals.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: Israel military official says 'preparing response' to Iran attack
item.description: on Saturday that the military is "preparing a response" to the Iranian missile barrage that targeted Israel earlier this week. "The IDF (Israeli military) is preparing a response to the unprecedented and unlawful Iranian attack on Israeli civilians and Israel," the military official said on condition of anonymity as he was not authorised to speak publicly on the issue.

item.title: Romania infringed on transgender man's rights, EU's top court rules
item.description: Romanian authorities' refusal to recognise the gender identity of a British-Romanian transgender man violated his rights, the EU's top court ruled. Arian Mirzarafie-Ahi, who transitioned after gaining British citizenship, faced denial from Romania despite EU law mandating recognition without extra procedures. This ruling sets a significant precedent for transgender rights across the EU.

item.title: Two migrants dead, many injured after van crashes in Croatia
item.description: In central Croatia, an overloaded van with German numberplates carrying migrants crashed, resulting in two fatalities and several injuries after veering off the road. The passengers included citizens of Turkey and Middle Eastern countries. This incident follows another migrant transport accident in Croatia last month, highlighting the ongoing migrant crisis along the Balkan route.

item.title: 'Command centre used to plan attacks': Israel strikes Hezbollah fighters inside Lebanon mosque
item.description: The Israeli Defense Forces conducted targeted airstrikes on Hezbollah forces operating from a command center inside a mosque near Salah Ghandour Hospital in southern Lebanon. The strikes aimed to halt terrorist activities against Israel. Nine medical and nursing personnel were injured despite prior evacuation warnings.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: Antarctica turning green 'dramatically', trend accelerated over years, study finds
item.description: Antarctica's vegetation cover has grown significantly, increasing from less than a square kilometre to nearly 12 square kilometres between 1986 and 2021. The accelerated greening, driven by climate change and reduced sea-ice extent, highlights the rapid and concerning transformation of the Antarctic Peninsula's landscape, emphasizing the urgent need for further research and action to protect this vulnerable region.

item.title: Hezbollah says fires rockets at north Israel air base
'War needs to end': Kamala Harris meets Arab American leaders amid growing discontent over US support for Israel
item.description: VP Kamala Harris met Arab American and Muslim leaders in Michigan to address US support concerns for Israel. The session, important for her presidential campaign, saw community leaders expressing frustrations over the humanitarian crisis in Gaza. Harris emphasised peace efforts amidst criticism. The upcoming election underscores the significance of this demographic's support.
